    "headerDoc": "STEP 885 — Hodge Conjecture: Partial Lean 4 Formal Skeleton\n  ============================================================\n\n  Hodge conjecture (Clay Millennium Problem): on a projective complex\n  smooth algebraic variety X, every rational Hodge class in\n  H^{2k}(X, ℚ) is a rational combination of classes of algebraic cycles.\n\n  Status:\n    - OPEN in full generality.\n    - Proved for k = 1 (Lefschetz's theorem on (1,1)-classes, 1924).\n    - Proved for k = dim X − 1 (dual via Poincaré duality).\n    - Proved for abelian varieties when simple (by Deligne, et al).\n    - Open for most of middle dime"
  },
